            h1.ui.header.large#learn-title
                .content
                    i.book.icon
                    | Warning Sign 5: Requests for Downloading security/diagnostic apps
            .ui.centered.stackable.grid
                .eight.wide.column
                    p Be very careful if someone on a call tells you to download software. They may say it’s to check for security or viruses on your computer.
                    h3 Don’t do it! The software could be malware, which is malicious and designed to cause damage. Hang up the call, and instead follow the approaches outlined below in Chapter 5.


                .eight.wide.column
                    h3 Audio Example
                    p Target: I am on TeamViewer.com right now. 
                    p Scammer: Okay, now sir I need you to move your arrow to the download button. Don’t click there, once your arrow is there, you have to download the previous version (version 7.x). And sir, whatever comes up you have to let me know. 
                    p Target: It’s asking me to download TeamViewer
                    p Scammer: Okay, just give that a double click. 
